# ICEPOT Framework

## I – Instruction

* **[Mandatory]** Generate test cases to calculate total price based on book price and quantity.
* **[Mandatory]** Generate test cases to apply discounts based on referral codes.
* **[Mandatory]** Generate test cases to add delivery charges to the final amount.
* **[Mandatory]** Generate test cases to display out-of-stock messages based on book availability.
* **[Mandatory]** Generate test cases to add, remove, and edit books available in the cart.
* **[Optional]** Generate test cases to display currently available discount details.
* **[High Priority]** Include both positive and negative test cases.
* **[Optional]** Generate test cases to validate timer limits for promo code discounts.

## C – Context

As a **Test Lead**, generate test cases to validate the **Cart Functionality** for an **Online Book Shop**. The validation should ensure accurate calculation of the total payable amount, application of discounts based on referral or promo codes, delivery charge calculation, stock availability checks, and cart management operations based on the number of books selected.

## E – Example

**Example Scenario:**

Apply **"WELCOME50"** discount to items in the cart for first-time users and verify that the discount is correctly reflected in the final payable amount.

## P – Persona

Generate the test cases from the perspective of a **Test Lead** with a focus on comprehensive coverage of critical cart functionalities.

## O – Output Format

Generate the output in **Gherkin format** using **Given–When–Then** syntax.

## T – Tone

The test cases should be **concise, professional, and easy to understand**, following industry-standard testing practices.

---

# Expected Output (Gherkin Format)

```gherkin
Feature: Validate Cart Functionality for Online Book Shop

  Background:
    Given the user has accessed the online book shop
    And books are available for purchase

  @Mandatory @HighPriority @Positive
  Scenario: Calculate total price based on price and quantity
    Given the user adds a book priced at ₹500 with quantity 3 to the cart
    When the cart total is calculated
    Then the total price should be ₹1500

  @Mandatory @HighPriority @Negative
  Scenario: Validate total price calculation with invalid quantity
    Given the user adds a book priced at ₹500 with quantity 0 to the cart
    When the cart total is calculated
    Then an error message "Invalid quantity selected" should be displayed

  @Mandatory @HighPriority @Positive
  Scenario: Apply discount using a valid referral code
    Given the user has books worth ₹2000 in the cart
    And the user enters a valid referral code "WELCOME50"
    When the discount is applied
    Then the applicable discount should be deducted from the total amount
    And the final payable amount should be displayed correctly

  @Mandatory @HighPriority @Negative
  Scenario: Apply discount using an invalid referral code
    Given the user has books worth ₹2000 in the cart
    When the user enters an invalid referral code "INVALID50"
    Then an error message "Referral code is invalid or expired" should be displayed
    And no discount should be applied

  @Mandatory @HighPriority @Positive
  Scenario: Add delivery charge to the final amount
    Given the user has books worth ₹1000 in the cart
    And a delivery charge of ₹50 is applicable
    When the final amount is calculated
    Then the payable amount should be ₹1050

  @Mandatory @HighPriority @Negative
  Scenario: Verify no delivery charge when free shipping criteria is met
    Given the user has books worth ₹3000 in the cart
    And free delivery is applicable for orders above ₹2500
    When the final amount is calculated
    Then no delivery charge should be added

  @Mandatory @HighPriority @Positive
  Scenario: Display out-of-stock message for unavailable books
    Given a selected book is unavailable in inventory
    When the user views the cart
    Then the status "Out of Stock" should be displayed
    And checkout should be restricted for that item

  @Mandatory @HighPriority @Negative
  Scenario: Prevent adding out-of-stock books to cart
    Given a book is marked as out of stock
    When the user attempts to add the book to the cart
    Then the system should prevent the addition
    And display the message "Book is currently unavailable"

  @Mandatory @HighPriority @Positive
  Scenario: Remove a book from the cart
    Given the user has books added to the cart
    When the user removes a selected book from the cart
    Then the book should be removed successfully
    And the cart total should be updated accordingly

  @Mandatory @HighPriority @Positive
  Scenario: Edit quantity of books in the cart
    Given the user has a book with quantity 1 in the cart
    When the user updates the quantity to 3
    Then the cart should reflect the updated quantity
    And the total amount should be recalculated correctly

  @Mandatory @HighPriority @Negative
  Scenario: Update cart with quantity exceeding available stock
    Given only 5 copies of a book are available
    When the user updates the quantity to 10
    Then the system should display the message "Requested quantity exceeds available stock"
    And the quantity should not be updated

  @Optional @Positive
  Scenario: Display available discount details in the cart
    Given active promotions are available
    When the user views the cart page
    Then all applicable discount offers should be displayed

  @Optional @Positive
  Scenario: Apply promo code within validity period
    Given the promo code "BOOK20" is active until 11:59 PM today
    When the user applies the promo code before expiry
    Then the discount should be applied successfully

  @Optional @Negative
  Scenario: Reject expired promo code based on timer limit
    Given the promo code "BOOK20" has expired
    When the user attempts to apply the promo code
    Then the system should display the message "Promo code has expired"
    And no discount should be applied
```
